Silvergate had to sell more bonds to repay the Federal Home Loan Bank loan,=
 so it booked more losses, so =E2=80=A6=C2=A0it is a close question, but it=
 seems possible that it now has a leverage ratio below 5% and so is not =E2=
=80=9Cwell capitalized.=E2=80=9D That is not technically the end of the wor=
ld =E2=80=94 if the number is above 4%, Silvergate would still be =E2=80=9C=
adequately capitalized=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it=E2=80=99s not great, =
and it=E2=80=99s pointing in the wrong direction.
If you are a bank you do not want to be pointing in the wrong direction, be=
cause that becomes self-fulfilling.   Bloomberg reports today:

Investors and business partners headed for the exits, with the stock down a=
