Stockholm and Helsinki.
Those trips were all for officials to attend meetings as members of private=
 equity firms=E2=80=99 limited partnership advisory councils, which have de=
veloped a reputation for taking place in posh, far-flung destinations.
=E2=80=9CI can=E2=80=99t remember an advisory committee meeting that wasn=
=E2=80=99t in a nice place,=E2=80=9D says Joseph John =E2=80=9CJ.J.=E2=80=
=9D Jelincic, a retired staffer and director of the California Public Emplo=
yees=E2=80=99 Retirement System. =E2=80=9CProbably the worst was Manhattan.=
=E2=80=9D
Such LPACs are supposed to be a means of giving state officials a voice in =
