<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic function of crypto is that you can b=
uy cryptocurrencies with dollars and sell cryptocurrencies for dollars. I s=
uppose <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30710887.25=
7420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9mZWF0dXJlcy8yMDIyLXRoZS1jcnlwdG8tc3=
RvcnkvP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3Nvd=
XJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMwMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb1864a36" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  there are other functions</a>? =
But the main thing is that if you think Bitcoin=C2=A0will go up, you spend =
some dollars to buy some Bitcoin, and then if it goes up (or doesn=E2=80=99=
t), you sell it for dollars.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you like crypto a lot =E2=80=94=C2=A0or if =
you are an institutional-ish crypto trader =E2=80=94 you will do this a lot=
, and you may find yourself frustrated with the=C2=A0<em>dollar=C2=A0</em>s=
ide of things. Crypto trades globally, 24 hours a day, seven days a week; y=
ou can use smart contracts to send crypto automatically, and sending crypto=
 is generally a permissionless lightly-regulated activity. But if you want =
to buy crypto with dollars, you need to use the US dollar financial system,=
 which can feel clunky to you, a crypto native. You will probably have to s=
end a bank transfer, but the banks are not open 24/7, and some of them migh=
t raise annoying questions if you try to transfer money from your bank acco=
unt to buy crypto.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are solutions. One solution is that you =
take your dollars, you deposit them at a big trustworthy crypto=C2=A0<em>ex=
change</em>, and then you use the dollars in your exchange account to buy a=
nd sell crypto. The exchange holds a bunch of dollars and a bunch of crypto=
 for its customers, and when you buy crypto the exchange deducts some dolla=
rs from your account and adds some crypto to your account, and vice versa w=
hen you sell. There are problems with this solution. The biggest is of cour=
se that sometimes the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGV=
zLzIwMjItMTEtMDkvYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1zLWZ0eC1oYWQtYS1kZWF0aC1zcGlyYWwtYmVmb3=
JlLWJpbmFuY2UtZGVhbD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzAyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtY=
WlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1v=
bmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcbdaa2cf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  big trustworthy</a=
> crypto exchanges=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjItMTItMTMvaG93LXRvLWRvLWZyYXVkLWF0LWEtZnV0dXJlcy1leGNoYW5nZT9jbXBp=
ZD1CQkQwMzAyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2x=
ldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB0bc2de19" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"><em>aren=E2=80=99t</em></a>, and they lose or=
 steal your dollars. But another issue is that, when you deposit your dolla=
rs at the exchange, <em>it=C2=A0</em>needs to deposit them somewhere. It ne=
eds to keep customer dollars at some crypto-friendly bank that will give th=
em back on demand.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another solution is stablecoins: Instead of ke=
eping your dollars at a bank, you turn them into=C2=A0<em>crypto dollars=C2=
=A0</em>by buying stablecoins that are meant to always be worth a dollar, a=
nd then instead of buying and selling crypto with dollars you buy and sell =
crypto with dollar-denominated stablecoins.=C2=A0But here too you have to t=
rust the stablecoin issuer, which is not always a great idea. (Other stable=
coins are algorithmic and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
