nts &amp; out of an abundance of caution,=E2=80=9D classic bank-run stuff. =
But that's not why they were withdrawing their money in late 2022, when the=
 trouble started.=C2=A0<em>Then</em>, they were withdrawing their money bec=
ause=C2=A0<em>crypto had collapsed:=C2=A0</em>Silvergate=E2=80=99s crypto-e=
xchange customers faced withdrawals from=C2=A0<em>their=C2=A0</em>customers=
, so they took their money out of Silvergate. The customers =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
crypto exchanges =E2=80=94=C2=A0were the problem, not Silvergate.</p>
