<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Deposits placed by a crypto-asset-related enti=
ty that are for the benefit of the crypto-asset-related entity=E2=80=99s cu=
stomers (end customers). The stability of such deposits may be driven by th=
e behavior of the end customer or crypto-asset sector dynamics, and not sol=
ely by the crypto-asset-related entity itself, which is the banking organiz=
ation=E2=80=99s direct counterparty. The stability of the deposits may be i=
nfluenced by, for example, periods of stress, market volatility, and relate=
d vulnerabilities in the crypto-asset sector, which may or may not be speci=
fic to the crypto-asset-related entity. Such deposits can be susceptible to=
 large and rapid inflows as well as outflows, when end customers react to=
=C2=A0crypto-asset-sector-related market events, media reports, and uncerta=
inty. This uncertainty and resulting deposit volatility can be exacerbated =
by end customer confusion related to inaccurate or misleading representatio=
ns of deposit insurance by a crypto-asset-related entity.</p>
</blockquote>
