<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Football governance</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A major-league=C2=A0professional sports team, =
as a <em>company</em>, is a weird combination of (1) a multibillion-dollar =
business and (2) some guy=E2=80=99s personal hobby. You would not expect th=
e corporate governance of the average sports team to be pristine, because a=
fter all it is generally a toy that a billionaire bought for himself to mak=
e watching sports more fun. On the other hand, because sports teams=C2=A0<e=
m>are=C2=A0</em>such big businesses, it is not uncommon for them to have mi=
nority owners: There=E2=80=99s the guy who is the =E2=80=9Cowner=E2=80=9D o=
f the team, the public face, the hobbyist in charge, and then there could b=
e=C2=A0a few other investors who also own smaller stakes in the team. They =
are also there mostly for hobbyist reasons, to be clear, and might prioriti=
ze, like, hanging out with the players over maximizing free cash flow. But =
they won=E2=80=99t want the team to spend money recklessly in ways that mai=
nly benefit the=C2=A0<em>majority=C2=A0</em>owner. Whereas the majority own=
er might think =E2=80=9Cthis is my toy and I can do whatever I want with it=
.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a very funny <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZXNwbi5jb20=
vbmZsL3N0b3J5L18vaWQvMzU3MjY2OTEvZm9ybWVyLXBhcnRuZXJzLXNheS1kYW4tc255ZGVyLX=
VzZWQtdGVhbS1mdW5kLWxpZmVzdHlsZS10b29rLWltcHJvcGVyLWxvYW4tdGhlaXItYXBwcm92Y=
Ww/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb6fe8631" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> ESPN story</a> about corpora=
te governance at the Washington Commanders of the National Football League,=
 whose majority owner is the controversial Daniel Snyder, but which also ha=
s some minority owners. The minority owners have things like a shareholder =
agreement specifying their rights=C2=A0and a board of directors that is sup=
posed to meet to oversee the team=E2=80=99s management, but really it is Sn=
yder=E2=80=99s team and the governance stuff doesn=E2=80=99t count for much=
. The problems here start with the fact that the=C2=A0team took out a $55 m=
illion credit line without board approval, but things snowball from there:<=
/p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The documents obtained by ESPN show that minor=
ity partners Robert Rothman, Dwight Schar and Frederick W. Smith protested =
the loan after they discovered it in a financial report's fine print. They =
then started looking closely into the team's finances and found Snyder was =
using the team as his "personal piggy bank," including charging the team $4=
.5 million to put its logo on his private jet, they alleged in the arbitrat=
ion petition filed with the NFL. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Rothman complained that the team's board =
had not met in years, Snyder responded, "What the f--- do I need a board me=
eting for?" according to the documents.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a June 5, 2020, letter, Snyder's lawyer tol=
d the partners that Snyder planned to expense more than $7 million in "unre=
imbursed business expenses" for fiscal years 2017 through 2020. Snyder also=
 revealed that he was seeking $1 million in reimbursements for vehicle cost=
s "and extra security required during foreign travel (due to his high-profi=
le position as Owner)."</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the letter, Snyder revealed that the expens=
es included a July 2018 yacht party in the south of France, where he hosted=
 fellow owners Jerry Jones of the Dallas Cowboys, Robert Kraft of the New E=
ngland Patriots and Terry Pegula of the Buffalo Bills.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"This included 'world-class cuisine prepared b=
y some of the top personal chefs in the world and the highest quality wine/=
beverages,'" the partners said in their petition. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The partners said they discovered Snyder had l=
eased his personal jets back to the team. Besides Snyder paying himself a s=
alary of $10 million a year, he also had arranged for the franchise to pay =
him a total of $4.5 million for having the team logo emblazoned on his pers=
onal jet. "An advertising fee," Snyder had called it, documents show.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The thing is that if you are the high-profile =
owner=C2=A0of a football team=C2=A0then in some sense everything you do rea=
lly=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>somehow on behalf of the team: You are the face o=
f the team, your yacht parties are team-related events, your jet has to be =
in team colors, etc. Your whole lifestyle is bound up with the team. And if=
 the team has some minority investors, well, they=E2=80=99re going to help =
pay for that lifestyle.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy93YXNoaW5n=
dG9uLWNvbW1hbmRlcnMtd29yc3QtdGVhbS1uZmxwYS1zdXJ2ZXktMzM1MzBlMTU_bW9kPWhwX2Z=
lYXRzdF9wb3M0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbd416746" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Elsewhere</a>: =E2=
=80=9CWashington=E2=80=99s football team, which owner Dan Snyder is explori=
ng selling, ranked last in a new survey conducted by the NFL Players Associ=
ation that rated teams in eight categories, including the treatment of play=
ers=E2=80=99 families, nutrition, the training staff and team travel. In th=
ree categories, the Commanders received an F- grade.=E2=80=9D</p>
<table class=3D"liveintent-flex-ad" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspac=
ing=3D"0" align=3D"center">
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"2">
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30710887.257420/aH=
R0cHM6Ly9zbGkuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9jbGljaz9zPTgyNTg4NSZsaT0zMDcxMDg4NyZtPTIxZ=
DZkZWE4MmQ2YjE2NjE1Y2Y0NDIzM2JlNjIwNTI1JnA9MzA5NjgzMDcmc3RwZT1kZWZhdWx0Jg/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cJ70ac247f" rel=3D"nofollow">
<img src=3D"https://sli.bloomberg.com/imp?s=3D825885&amp;li=3D30710887&amp;=
m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&amp;p=3D30968307&amp;stpe=3Ddefault&am=
p;" border=3D"0" width=3D"550" style=3D"width: 100%; max-width: 550px; disp=
lay:block" />
</a>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Elsewhere in private jets</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess if you are the chief executive officer=
 of a company it is just a good business decision to buy a private jet? For=
 yourself, I mean, with your own money, not for the company. The trade is t=
hat you buy the jet for yourself, you use it to fly around to business meet=
ings, and you=C2=A0<em>charge your company=C2=A0</em>for the use of the jet=
. You do enough meetings and the jet pays for itself, with shareholder mone=
y. This is not exactly=C2=A0<em>legal</em>, but <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZ=
XdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy00Mw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe7df1955" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> here we are</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission today a=
nnounced settled charges against Oregon-based freight transportation supply=
 company, The Greenbrier Companies Inc., and its founder and former CEO and=
 Chairman, William A. Furman, for failing to disclose perks provided to Fur=
man and other Greenbrier executives and compensation Furman received from G=
reenbrier=E2=80=99s charters of Furman=E2=80=99s private plane for travel b=
y company executives, including Furman. Greenbrier and Furman agreed to pay=
 $1 million and $100,000 in civil penalties, respectively, to settle the ch=
arges.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s orders find that Furman owne=
d a private aircraft, which he leased to an aircraft management company to =
charter to third parties on his behalf. According to the orders, during fis=
cal years 2017 to 2021, Greenbrier paid the management company approximatel=
y $3 million to charter Furman=E2=80=99s plane for business-related travel,=
 but Greenbrier did not disclose that Furman received approximately $1.6 mi=
llion of that amount.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I bet he=E2=80=99s kicking himself that it nev=
er occurred to him to put the company=E2=80=99s logo on the jet and charge =
extra for that.</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Private equity boondoggles</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you run a private equity fund that seeks in=
vestment from state pension funds, you will want to have some sort of gover=
nance board that includes representatives from those pension funds, not jus=
t =E2=80=94=C2=A0not primarily =E2=80=94=C2=A0as a governance tool but also=
 s a marketing tool, a way to maintain friendly relationships with the pens=
ion funds who give you money. You=E2=80=99ll invite the representatives to =
meetings, schmooze with them, make them feel included, help them understand=
 and appreciate what you are doing, make them feel good about your fund and=
 the relationship. Will you share a nice meal with them, at these meetings?=
 Will you pick up the check? Will the meetings be in Tuscany? Oh sure. Bloo=
mberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30=
710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtM=
DItMjgvdHVzY2FueS1mb3ItMjAwLXByaXZhdGUtZXF1aXR5LXN1YnNpZGl6ZXMtcGVuc2lvbi1m=
dW5kLWx1eHVyeT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzAyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV=
0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAzMDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3=
R1ZmYjeGo0eTd2emtn/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb2ed9583" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Neil Weinber=
g reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two Michigan pension fund officials attended a=
 2018 Apax Partners event at the Four Seasons Hotel in Florence, Italy, tha=
t featured =E2=80=9Ccustom tailored activities and itineraries,=E2=80=9D in=
cluding tours of the Tuscan countryside on vintage Vespa scooters and a gal=
a dinner at the 17th Century Villa le Corti.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The bill for the state: less than $200 for eac=
h official, according to public records obtained by Bloomberg. And Michigan=
 is hardly alone in letting private equity firms foot most of the bill for =
luxury travel and trips by state pension fund managers, who are public empl=
oyees.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gaw Capital paid for most of the $21,127 busin=
ess-class airfare for an Illinois fund official attending its 2018 meeting =
at the Renaissance Resort in Okinawa, Japan =E2=80=94 the state paid just $=
392. Florida officials visited Milan, Rome and Paris last June, courtesy of=
 JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. funds. Other funds have since covered Florida off=
icials=E2=80=99 trips to London, Stockholm and Helsinki.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those trips were all for officials to attend m=
eetings as members of private equity firms=E2=80=99 limited partnership adv=
isory councils, which have developed a reputation for taking place in posh,=
 far-flung destinations.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI can=E2=80=99t remember an advisory =
committee meeting that wasn=E2=80=99t in a nice place,=E2=80=9D says Joseph=
 John =E2=80=9CJ.J.=E2=80=9D Jelincic, a retired staffer and director of th=
e California Public Employees=E2=80=99 Retirement System. =E2=80=9CProbably=
 the worst was Manhattan.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Such LPACs are supposed to be a means of givin=
g state officials a voice in how the firms invest public money. But some wo=
rry that the luxurious trips may unduly influence the officials who are tre=
ated to them.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably=C2=A0the LPAC could do its governan=
ce and advisory work over email and Zoom, and honestly that seems like it w=
ould be more convenient for a lot of these pension funds. But imagine being=
 the first private equity firm to announce that change.=C2=A0</p>
