<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Incredible <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZ=
XdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMDIvamltLWNyYW1lci1ldGZzLWFycml2ZS10by1iZXQtb24t=
YWdhaW5zdC1tYWQtbW9uZXktaG9zdC1zLXBpY2tzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMDIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZ=
GJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMwMi=
Z1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8a591baa" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>  bit here</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whether you=E2=80=99re a lover or loather of J=
im Cramer =E2=80=94 and on both Wall Street and Main Street, there are plen=
ty of each =E2=80=94 you=E2=80=99re now able to express that view via the m=
agic of ETFs.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A pair of new products is launching Thursday t=
hat will help US investors bet either on or against the stock picks of the =
host of CNBC=E2=80=99s Mad Money show, arguably the world=E2=80=99s most-fa=
mous financial pundit. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Matthew Tuttle, CEO of Tuttle Capital Manageme=
nt, has turned his attention to Cramer, fulfilling a long-running finance j=
oke that the CNBC anchor should get his own inverse fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf he specifically says either buy, b=
uy, buy a stock, then we=E2=80=99re gonna go short that stock at the next p=
ractical moment,=E2=80=9D Tuttle told Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Trillions podcast=
, referring to the inverse strategy. =E2=80=9CIf he tells you he hates a st=
ock or sell, sell, sell or something like that, then we=E2=80=99re gonna go=
 long that name again at the next kind of practical entry point.=E2=80=9D .=
..</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The methodology behind the ETFs is decidedly l=
ow-tech. To design the portfolios, which are equal weight, Tuttle and two c=
olleagues watch Cramer=E2=80=99s television appearances throughout the day =
and monitor his Twitter account. The result is two actively managed portfol=
ios that hold between 20 to 50 names with a high turnover rate, Tuttle said=
. Both products carry an expense ratio of 1.2%.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They=E2=80=99re called LJIM and SJIM, for long=
 and short, respectively. Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY3JhbWVyZXRmcy5jb20v/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB05519c62" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the website</a>. Here is <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30710887.257420/aHR0cHM6Ly91cG=
xvYWRzLXNzbC53ZWJmbG93LmNvbS82MzcyNDBhNDliYTU2ZjdiZmJlODJjODQvNjNmZjcyYTE4N=
DU5NzY4ZjVlM2Q3NDA2X1ByaW50ZXIlMjAtJTIwQ3JhbWVyJTIwRVRGcyUyMENvbWJpbmVkJTIw=
Mi0yMS0yMyUyMFBybyUyMC0lMjB2Mi5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB06e62cef" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> the prospectus for SJIM</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investment Objective: The Inverse =
Cramer Tracker ETF (the =E2=80=9CFund=E2=80=9D) seeks to provide investment=
s results that are approximately the opposite of, before fees and expenses,=
 the results of the investments recommended by television personality Jim C=
ramer.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh yeah.</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Fund=E2=80=99s adviser monitor=
s Cramer=E2=80=99s stock selection and overall market recommendations throu=
ghout the trading day as publicly announced on Twitter or his television pr=
ograms broadcast on CNBC and sells Cramer=E2=80=99s stock recommendations s=
hort. The Fund goes short or long on stocks or ETFs, including Index ETFs a=
nd inverse Index ETFs, to take the opposite side of Cramer=E2=80=99s announ=
ced market or sector view. The Fund=E2=80=99s portfolio is comprised genera=
lly of=C2=A020 to 50 equity securities of any market capitalization of dome=
stic and foreign issuers through American Depositary Receipts, and/or ETFs =
if Cramer makes market or sector recommendations. Should Cramer recommend b=
uying any of the securities in the Fund=E2=80=99s portfolio, the Fund will =
dispose of those holdings. Should Cramer recommend selling any of the secur=
ities in the Fund=E2=80=99s portfolio, the Fund will keep those holdings. T=
he adviser may also sell securities that have gone =E2=80=9Cstale=E2=80=9D=
=E2=80=94i.e., have been held for several weeks with no further commentary =
by Cramer. If Cramer does not take=C2=A0any view on any of the securities i=
n the Fund=E2=80=99s portfolio, including when he is absent from CNBC or Tw=
itter for any reason, the adviser further retains discretion to sell positi=
ons if market conditions such as large swings in either direction necessita=
te a sale because profit or loss targets are met and replace them with secu=
rities that represent the opposite side of Cramer=E2=80=99s announced marke=
t or sector view. Under normal circumstances, the Fund will hold positions =
no longer than a 5-day trading week but could hold a position longer if Cra=
mer continues to have a contrary opinion.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I feel like this is what the financial industr=
y is all about? I love it. The prospectus is notably short on backtest data=
 (there is none), presumably because it is hard to do a backtest on the str=
ategy, presumably=C2=A0because no one was sitting around making notes of al=
l of Cramer=E2=80=99s recommendations for months=C2=A0<em>before=C2=A0</em>=
launching this thing. It is very funny to have a job that is just sitting a=
round watching Jim Cramer=E2=80=99s show all day and doing the opposite of =
every trade he recommends, but you probably wouldn=E2=80=99t do it if you w=
eren=E2=80=99t getting paid 1.2%.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean! You might do it if it had alpha? It=C2=
=A0<em>is </em>=E2=80=9Ca long-running finance joke=E2=80=9D that doing the=
 opposite of Cramer=E2=80=99s recommendations could make you money. Presuma=
bly at some point some bored young person dreaming of making it as a stock =
trader tried to actually do it? Watch TV, do the opposite of Cramer=E2=80=
=99s trades, get rich? Presumably that person did not get rich?=C2=A0Presum=
ably if it worked people would just do it, instead of selling it as an ETF;=
 in general this is not a perfect heuristic but it feels right here. Especi=
ally since both SJIM and LJIM exist, and they can=E2=80=99t really=C2=A0<em=
>both=C2=A0</em>work. The point of these products is not that Cramer=E2=80=
=99s recommendations have positive or negative alpha; the point is that (1)=
 the products are funny and (2) people might buy them for comedy and/or cel=
ebrity reasons?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, from the prospectus:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Trust, the Fund and the advise=
r are not affiliated with Cramer or any of the media by which his recommend=
ations are communicated. Cramer is not involved in the creation, management=
 or operations of the Fund. The adviser does not in all cases perform funda=
mental investment analysis of securities bought, sold and held by the Fund.=
 The primary factor for transacting in such securities or related securitie=
s is the fact that they are mentioned by Cramer.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Surely if one of these funds consistently outp=
erforms the market, Cramer should stop giving away free alpha to Tuttle and=
 start running his own fund (or inverse fund) himself? It would be funny if=
 it was the inverse one.=C2=A0</p>
